{"id":"six_minute_walk_distance","version":"0.0.4","templates":[{"id":"six_minute_walk_distance","version":"0.0.1"}],"language":"en","updated":"2021-08-12T12:38:27+02:00","authors":[{"name":"Núria Rodríguez Ruiz","email":"nuria.ruiz@cambio.se"}],"format":"CambioForm.v1","name":"Six Minute Walk Distance","actions":[{"condition":"expected_6_minute_walk && (age <= 40 || age >= 80)","assignments":["expected_6_minute_walk = '' ","lower_limit_of_normal_6mwd = ''","percentage_of_expected_6mwd = ''","height_1 = ''","weight_1 = ''",""]}],"guidelines":[{"condition":"gender && height && weight && age && observed_distance_walked","execution":[{"id":"Six_Minute_Walk_Distance","version":"1"}]}],"elements":[{"type":"form","children":[{"type":"container","hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"type":"row","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"type":"column","spanlarge":12,"spanmedium":8,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"text":"## 6-Minute Walk Distance (6MWD)\n\nThe 6-Minute Walk Distance (6MWD) is a tool to quickly assess physical function and an important component of quality of life, as well as to reflect the capacity to undertake day-to-day activities. 6MWD can be used in these several conditions: 1. to assess response to interventions in patients with moderate to severe heart or lung disease 2. to measure functional status in patients who are elderly, frail, arthritis, neuromuscular disorders, and/or otherwise unable to tolerate treadmill exercise tests. Use in patients between the ages of 40-80.","type":"text","size":"m","position":"left"}]},{"type":"column","spanlarge":6,"spanmedium":4,"spansmall":4,"hidden":false,"readonly":false,"children":[{"text":"Input","type":"text","size":"m","position":"left"},{"type":"input-select","label":"Gender","name":"gender","options":[{"text":"Male","value":"at0005"},{"text":"Female","value":"at0006"}],"clearable":true,"display":"buttons","hidden":false,"reado